### **💡 Web Game Dev Tips for this Structure:**
*   **Keep the Scope Tight:** You really only need 4 or 5 main 3D rooms (Medical Bay, Bridge, Lab, Airlock). You can make the game feel huge just by changing the lighting in these rooms (e.g., stark white at the start, warm yellow when Rocky arrives, flashing red during the climax).
*   **Visual Contrast:** Make the present-day spaceship scenes cool-toned (blues, whites, sterile) and the Earth flashbacks warm-toned (sepia, golden hour, cozy) to clearly differentiate the timelines.
*   **Animating Rocky:** Rendering and animating a complex 5-legged alien in a browser game might be difficult. You can cleverly obscure Rocky behind slightly frosted/scratched Xenonite glass, representing him mostly through shadowy silhouettes, gestures, and his musical UI popping up on the screen!
